This paper deals with imitation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses the problem of domain adaptation, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of generative models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of aligning MDPs, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control).
